Reading guide
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────[0m

[2;37m# The shape is the same as `three_hashes.yaml`:[0m
[2;37m# - Alice opens a tuplespace, writes a few tuples, exits.[0m
[2;37m# - Bob opens the same path, reads them back.[0m
[2;37m# - The harness asserts what Bob recovered equals what Alice[0m
[2;37m# stored.[0m

[2;37m# The new piece is the `durable: true` flag on each `out`. Tuples[0m
[2;37m# without it stay in memory and don't survive Alice's exit. The[0m
[2;37m# demo proves both: durable tuples come back; non-durable ones[0m
[2;37m# don't.[0m

[1;33m════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
