════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════[0m

[2;36m# source: Alice's three out() calls[0m
[2;37m```fmpl[0m
[0;37mworld.out(%{type: :room, data: %{name: "Rusty Flagon"}, durable: true})[0m
[0;37mworld.out(%{type: :menu, data: %{ale: 3, mead: 5}, durable: true})[0m
[0;37mworld.out(%{type: :note, data: "scratch — should NOT survive"})[0m
[2;37m```[0m
[2;37m# Two durable tuples (`:room`, `:menu`) and one ephemeral note. The `durable: true` flag opts each tuple into write-through to the backing fjall keyspace; without it, the tuple lives only in memory.[0m
[0;36m[alice][0m [0;32mfmpl> [0mworld.out(%{type: :room, data: %{name: "Rusty Flagon"}, durable: true})
[1;35m=> null[0m
[0;36m[alice][0m [0;32mfmpl> [0mworld.out(%{type: :menu, data: %{ale: 3, mead: 5}, durable: true})
[1;35m=> null[0m
[0;36m[alice][0m [0;32mfmpl> [0mworld.out(%{type: :note, data: "scratch — should NOT survive"})
[1;35m=> null[0m

